Acadia National Park Region CBC Results

Nick Fisichelli and Kyle Lima

4/3/2022

Summary Statistics

53% decline in total count of birds recorded on the CBCs since 1971. 43% decline in count of birds per party hour since 1971.

Example plot




Species Trend Table

The species trend is based soley on the count/party hour estimate and p-value. There are a lot more determinable trends in the count data, but I think we want to use the count/party hour metric to account for effort.

There are 33 increasing species, 42 decreasing species, and 51 that have shown no change over the last 51 years. The other 36 species did not have enough data to determine a trend, beacuse they are rarely detected species (vagrants, unusual overwinterers, or irruptive species).
